    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - Meritor Medium Duty Front Drive Steer Axle - Prepare Parts for Assembly -
        Silicone (RTV) Gasket Material Application
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Silicone (RTV) Gasket Material Application</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Take care when you use silicone gasket materials to avoid serious personal injury. Follow the
                        manufacturer's instructions to prevent irritation to the eyes and skin.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The following silicone gasket products or their equivalent can be used on Meritor
                        components:
                    </para>
                    <seqlist>
                        <item>
                            <para>Loctite&#174; Ultra Grey Adhesive/Sealant #18581</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>ThreeBond No. 1216</para>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <para>Meritor</para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Part No. 2297Z7046, 50 lb. (22.7 kg) container</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Part No. 2297B7022, 10 oz. (300 ml) cartridge</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Part No. 2297A7021, 3 oz. (85 g) tube</para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                        </item>
                    </seqlist>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Application</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove all old gasket material from both surfaces.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the surfaces where the silicone gasket material will be applied. Remove all oil,
                    grease, dirt and moisture.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Dry both surfaces.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>The amount of silicone gasket material applied must not exceed a 0.125-inch (3.18 mm) diameter
                        bead. Too much gasket material can block lubrication passages and result in damage to the
                        components.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a 0.125-inch (3.18 mm) diameter continuous bead of silicone gasket material around
                    one surface. Also apply the gasket material around the edge of all the fastener holes on that
                    surface (Figure 35).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0201235" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201235.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. Apply Gasket Material</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. 0.125 INCH (3.18 MM) DIAMETER SILICONE GASKET MATERIAL BEAD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Assemble the components immediately to permit the gasket material to compress evenly
                    between the parts. Tighten the fasteners to the required torque value for that size fastener. Refer
                    to
                    <hotlnk document="s02012_59.xml" xrefid="x0201201">Fastener Torque Chart</hotlnk>. There is no
                    special procedure or additional torque required.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wait 20 minutes before filling the assembly with lubricant.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
